column.comment: The serialized description of this link - used for admin pages and title attribute. May be a TranslatableMarkup.

column.comment: The class for this link plugin.

column.comment: A serialized array of URL options, such as a query string or HTML attributes.

column.name: provider
column.comment: The name of the module that generated this link.

column.name: enabled
column.comment: A flag for whether the link should be rendered in menus. (0 = a disabled menu item that may be shown on admin screens, 1 = a normal, visible link)

column.name: discovered
column.comment: A flag for whether the link was discovered, so can be purged on rebuild

column.name: expanded
column.comment: Flag for whether this link should be rendered as expanded in menus - expanded links always have their child links displayed, instead of only when the link is in the active trail (1 = expanded, 0 = not expanded)

column.name: weight
column.comment: Link weight among links in the same menu at the same depth.

column.name: metadata
column.comment: A serialized array of data that may be used by the plugin instance.

column.name: has_children
column.comment: Flag indicating whether any enabled links have this link as a parent (1 = enabled children exist, 0 = no enabled children).

column.name: depth
column.comment: The depth relative to the top level. A link with empty parent will have depth == 1.

column.name: p1
